The paper discusses the use of neural networks for link prediction in dynamic graphs for recommendation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of temporal contextual information, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SOC). The experiments are performed on datasets, which is relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of changes in user-item relationships over time, which is relevant to social networks (cs.SOC).
